# Native iOS client parity

This repo is WhoSmarter (Next.js on Netlify): **backend + shared game server** for multiplayer quiz.

A separate native **Swift iOS app** ([native_streamquiz](https://github.com/severin12am/native_streamquiz)) uses the **same** Supabase project and **same** deployed API. Do not break API routes, Supabase schema, Realtime channels, or phase/timing behavior without considering iOS parity.

**Authoritative spec:** `PROJECT.md` (state machine, DB, APIs). `ios_implementation_help.md` has extra mobile parity notes (RN-oriented; API/DB/phase flow still apply to Swift).

